pected Result: Zapier shows \"Test Successful\" with captured JSON\n\ufe0f Phase 2: Notion Database Setup\nStep 2.1: Create Target Database\nDatabase Name: \ud83d\udd2e AI Sacred Events Log\nRequired Properties:\n[nested content]\nStep 2.2: Create Database in Notion\nQuick Creation: Use the database template below or create manually\nManual Creation Steps:\nIn this Notion page, type /database \u2192 Database - Inline\nTitle: \"\ud83d\udd2e AI Sacred Events Log\"\nAdd all properties from table above\nConfigure Status property options:\n[nested content]\nConfigure Actor select options:\n[nested content]\nPhase 3: Connect Zapier to Notion\nStep 3.1: Add Notion Action\nIn your Zap, click + Add Action\nSearch: Notion\nSelect: Create Database Item\nClick Continue\nStep 3.2: Authenticate with Notion Token\nClick + Add new account\nPaste integration token: [SCRUBBED:notion_token]\nName connection: \"AI Workflow Coordinator\"\nClick Yes, Continue to Notion\nStep 3.3: Configure Database Mapping\nSelect Database: \ud83d\udd2e AI Sacred Events Log\nField Mappings (use Zapier's dynamic fields from webhook):\n[nested content]\nStep 3.4: Test Action\nClick Test Action\nVerify new item appears in Notion database\nCheck all fields populated correctly\n\ufe0f Phase 4: Security & Filtering\nStep 4.1: Add Protocol Validation Filter\nBetween Trigger and Action:\nClick + between Webhook and Notion steps\nAdd Filter by Zapier\nConfigure:\n[nested content]\nPurpose: Reject unauthorized or malformed requests\nStep 4.2: Add Custom Header Validation (Advanced)\nOptional but Recommended: Requires Zapier Code step (Python/JavaScript)\nAdd Code by Zapier step:\nStep 4.3: Rate Limiting Configuration\nZapier Built-in: Max 1 webhook/second on free plan\nRecommended: Implement delay for batch operations\nAdd Delay by Zapier (optional):\nDelay: 2 seconds\nPurpose: Prevent Notion API rate limits (3 req/sec)\nPhase 5: Testing Protocol\nTest Case 1: Successful Transpilation Event\nExpected: Green success entry in Notion database\nTest Case 2: Error/Failure Event\nExpected: Red failure entry + trigger error alert (if configured)\nTest Case 3: Invalid Protocol (Should Be Rejected)", "label": "general", "tongue": "DR", "curriculum": "practitioner", "quality": 1.0, "complexity": 4.667, "phdm_category": "unknown", "content_hash": "abc700952c9f665f", "timestamp": 1774179250.027703}
 {"instruction": "What is AIStream/Aethermore Master Research & Development Plan and how does it function within SCBE-AETHERMOORE?", "output": "EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\nProject Goals:\nBuild AIStream: Multi-AI personality platform with 3D animated avatars (Futurama-style)\nBackground audio system for project tracking and updates\nIntelligent task monitoring with Zapier automation\nReddit Devvit app for Developer Funds opportunity\nAI Weight Training Device concept (utilizing 6 computer senses)\nRobust, professional-grade code with extensive features\nPHASE 1: RESEARCH DELEGATION FRAMEWORK\nAI Research Team Assignment:\nChatGPT-4 - Multi-AI architecture patterns, conversational AI best practices\nClaude (Anthropic) - Code quality, safety patterns, robust implementation\nGemini - Real-time streaming, TTS/audio processing, Firebase integration\nPerplexity - Current AI research papers, industry trends, Reddit Devvit documentation\nNotion AI - Project structure optimization, documentation standards\nFirebase Studio AI - Real-time database patterns, authentication flows\nZapier Copilot - Workflow automation, intelligent monitoring systems\nPHASE 2: CORE RESEARCH AREAS\n2.1 Multi-AI Personality Systems\nLead AI: ChatGPT-4Research Questions:\nHow do leading conversational AI platforms handle multiple personality contexts?\nWhat are best practices for personality consistency across sessions?\nMemory management for long-term personality coherence\nSwitching mechanisms between AI personalities\nDeliverable: Architecture document for multi-AI personality system\n2.2 3D Avatar Integration & Animation\nLead AI: Gemini + PerplexityResearch Questions:\nBest 3D avatar libraries for web (Three.js, Babylon.js, Ready Player Me)\nReal-time lip-sync from TTS audio streams\nPerformance optimization for browser-based 3D rendering\nCharacter animation state machines\nDeliverable: Technical specification for 3D avatar system\n2.3 Real-Time Audio Streaming Architecture\nLead AI: GeminiResearch Questions:\nFirebase Realtime Database vs Firestore for audio streaming\nWebRTC vs WebSocket for low-latency audio\nTTS API comparison (Google Cloud TTS, ElevenLabs, Azure)\nBackground audio playback patterns\nDeliverable: Audio streaming implementation guide\n2.4 Intelligent Task Monitoring System\nLead AI: Zapier Copilot + ClaudeResearch Questions:\nZapier best practices for multi-step workflows\nPrompt engineering for detailed, specific, researched responses\nTimer-based check-ins and status updates\nJira\u2192GitHub\u2192AI review\u2192notification pipelines\nDeliverable: Zapier workflow templates with intelligent monitoring\n2.5 Reddit Devvit App Development\nLead AI: Perplexity + ClaudeResearch Questions:\nReddit Devvit framework documentation and examples\nDeveloper Funds application requirements and timeline\nBest practices for Reddit community engagement\nMVP feature set for rapid deployment\nDeliverable: Reddit Devvit MVP specification and timeline\n2.6 AI Weight Training Device Concept\nLead AI: Claude + ChatGPT-4Research Questions:\nSix senses for computer AI (vision, audio, text, sensor data, network patterns, temporal/timing)\nTraining methodologies for multi-modal AI systems\nBenchmark datasets for each sensory modality\nIntegration with existing AIStream architecture\nDeliverable: Conceptual framework for AI training device\n2.7 Code Quality & Robustness\nLead AI: ClaudeResearch Questions:\nTypeScript best practices for large-scale applications\nTesting strategies (unit, integration, e2e)\nError handling and resilience patterns\nPerformance monitoring and optimization\nDeliverable: Code quality standards document\nPHASE 3: TECHNICAL STACK RESEARCH\n3.1 Frontend Framework Analysis\nResearch:\nReact 19+ features and performance\nNext.js 15+ for SSR and streaming\nState management (Zustand vs Jotai vs Redux Toolkit)\nUI component libraries (Tailwind, shadcn/ui)\n3.2 Backend & Database\nResearch:\nFirebase services integration (Auth, Firestore, Functions, Storage)\nEdge functions for low-latency AI responses\nDatabase schema design for multi-AI conversations\nScalability patterns\n3.", "label": "general", "tongue": "DR", "curriculum": "architect", "quality": 1.0, "complexity": 4.0, "phdm_category": "unknown", "content_hash": "8404cfed6e768738", "timestamp": 1774179250.028376}
 {"instruction": "Describe Research publishing options (traditional, self-publishing) and its role in the architecture.", "output": "Book Review Notes\nTo create a comprehensive book review, I should analyze the following elements:\nContent Analysis\nPlot summary: Brief overview without major spoilers\nCharacter development: Depth, believability, and growth of main characters\nWorld-building: How effectively the setting is established\nThemes and messages: Key ideas explored in the work\nWriting style: Prose quality, dialogue, pacing, and narrative structure\nCritical Evaluation\nStrengths: What works well in the book\nWeaknesses: Areas that could be improved\nComparisons: How it relates to other works in the genre\nTarget audience: Who would enjoy this book most\nReview Format\nIntroduction: Book details, author, and initial impression\nBody: Analysis of plot, characters, themes, and writing style\nConclusion: Overall assessment and recommendation\nRating: Numerical or star rating if applicable", "label": "general", "tongue": "DR", "curriculum": "master", "quality": 1.0, "complexity": 3.0, "phdm_category": "unknown", "content_hash": "0bd0c4a8dcda7726", "timestamp": 1774179250.02869}
